properties.history:
A lost port at the entrance to Pagham or Selsey harbour. (A. Mawer and F.M. Stenton eds., 'Place-Names of Sussex', (Cambridge, 1929) i, p. 96) The grid references are given to the entrance to Pagham harbour. See also Pagham and Selsey, Sussex (q.v.). See Lindsay 
      Fleming,History of Pagham, vol 1 (Ditchling, 1949), esp. pp. 46–8; 
      53–7; 184–9.
